 RIGHT THING, THE (riet thing, dh@) n. That which is "obviously" the correct
or appropriate thing to use, do, say, etc. Use of this term often implies
that in fact reasonable people may disagree. "Never let your conscience keep
you from doing the right thing!" "What's the right thing for LISP to do when
it reads '(.)'?" Antonym: THE WRONG THING (q.v.).